# deep6 ‚Äî AI Agent Rules

## Project identity

deep6 is a no-dependency ES6 mini-library for advanced deep equivalence, unification, and cloning of JavaScript structures. It supports extensible pattern matching, deep cloning with circular reference handling, and traversing complex objects including Map, Set, typed arrays, symbols, and property descriptors.

## Critical rules

- **ES6 modules.** The project is `"type": "module"`. Use `import`/`export` syntax.
- **Zero runtime dependencies.** Do not add packages to `dependencies`.
- **Do not modify or delete test expectations** without understanding why they changed.
- **Do not add comments or remove comments** unless explicitly asked.
- **Keep `src/` in sync.** Run `npm test` to verify after changes.

## Code style

- 2-space indentation.
- Single quotes for strings.
- Semicolons are required (enforced by Prettier).
- See `.prettierrc` for formatting settings.

## Architecture quick reference

- **Main entry:** `src/index.js` exports `equal`, `clone`, `match`, `any`, `_`.
- **Unification core:** `src/unify.js` ‚Äî the heart of the library. Uses a non-recursive stack-based algorithm.
- **Environment:** `src/env.js` ‚Äî `Env`, `Variable`, `Unifier` classes for unification state management.
- **Traversing:** `src/traverse/` ‚Äî object walking and cloning.
  - `walk.js` ‚Äî generic non-recursive object walker with registry/filter system.
  - `clone.js` ‚Äî deep cloning using the walker.
  - `preprocess.js` ‚Äî pattern preprocessing for matching.
  - `assemble.js` ‚Äî object assembly utilities.
  - `deref.js` ‚Äî dereferencing utilities.
- **Unifiers:** `src/unifiers/` ‚Äî pattern matching components.
  - `matchString.js` ‚Äî regex-based string matching.
  - `matchTypeOf.js` ‚Äî type-based matching.
  - `matchInstanceOf.js` ‚Äî instanceof-based matching.
  - `matchCondition.js` ‚Äî conditional matching.
  - `ref.js` ‚Äî reference variables.
- **Utils:** `src/utils/` ‚Äî utility functions.

## Verification commands

- `npm test` ‚Äî run the test suite.
- `npm run debug` ‚Äî run tests with Node inspector.
- `npm run ts-check` ‚Äî TypeScript type checking.
- `npm run lint` ‚Äî Prettier check.
- `npm run lint:fix` ‚Äî Prettier write.

## File layout

- Entry point: `src/index.js`
- Core: `src/unify.js`, `src/env.js`
- Traverse: `src/traverse/` (walk.js, clone.js, preprocess.js, assemble.js, deref.js)
- Unifiers: `src/unifiers/` (matchString.js, matchTypeOf.js, matchInstanceOf.js, matchCondition.js, ref.js)
- Utils: `src/utils/` (replaceVars.js)
- Tests: `tests/tests.js` (main test file), `tests/server.js`

## When reading the codebase

- Start with `ARCHITECTURE.md` for the module map and dependency graph.
- `src/unify.js` is the core ‚Äî read it first to understand the unification algorithm.
- `src/env.js` defines `Env`, `Variable`, and `Unifier` classes.
- `src/traverse/walk.js` is the foundation for all traversal operations.
- Read `README.md` for usage examples.
